hackathon-description-text: Hack HW is Harvard-Westlake's third annual hackathon. It is a fantastic oppurtunity for 9th- 12th grade students to practice the skills learned in the classroom. They can apply it to real world issues and create solutions with the use of technology. Students are allowed to use any language and platform for their projects as long as they are a solution to some issue. The hackathon lasts 36 hours. Intermingled with the coding, students will have the option to hear from various speakers in the event.
hackathon-eligibility: Harvard-Westlake students signed up for the hackathon may participate.
hackathon-requirements:
Make sure to add: 
- actual program
- photos
hackathon-rules: All projects have to be new ideas that have not been worked on previously.
